<subSubSection box="[151,1266,1404,1426]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1266,1404,1426]" box="[151,1266,1404,1426]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,276,1404,1426]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Type taxon.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="(Muller &amp; Troschel, 1842)" authorityName="Muller &amp; Troschel" authorityYear="1842" baseAuthorityName="Muller &amp; Troschel" baseAuthorityYear="1842" box="[283,802,1404,1426]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiuridae" genus="Ophioplocus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="imbricatus">
<emphasis box="[283,528,1404,1426]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Ophioplocus imbricatus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Muller, J. X. &amp; Troschel, F. H." bookContentInfo="134 pp." box="[540,795,1404,1426]" journalOrPublisher="Vieweg, Braunschweig" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" refId="ref52005" refString="Muller, J. X. &amp; Troschel, F. H. (1842) System der Asteriden. Vieweg, Braunschweig, xx + 134 pp." title="System der Asteriden" type="book" year="1842">Müller &amp; Troschel, 1842</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
originally described as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Müller &amp; Troschel" authorityYear="1842" box="[1044,1261,1404,1426]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiuridae" genus="Ophiolepis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="imbricata">
<emphasis box="[1044,1261,1404,1426]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Ophiolepis imbricata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,1470,1963]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1470,1495]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Disc covered by irregular and imbricated plates. Radial shields oval and smaller (approximately one tenth of dd), separated by several scales. One apical papilla. The number of lateral oral papillae variable, usually eight to ten. Bursal slits smaller, often bordered by papillae or scales. Dorsal arm plates divided into two or more. Two to seven tentacle scales in the first arm segment. Two to five arm spines arranged along the outer edge of the lateral arm plates (
<bibRefCitation author="Lyman, T." bookContentInfo="203 pp." box="[358,504,1614,1639]" journalOrPublisher="University Press: Welch, Bigelow, &amp; Company, Cambridge" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" refId="ref50591" refString="Lyman, T. (1865) Ophiuridae and Astrophytidae. University Press: Welch, Bigelow, &amp; Company, Cambridge, 203 pp." title="Ophiuridae and Astrophytidae" type="book" year="1865">Lyman 1865</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Tommasi, L. R." box="[516,685,1614,1639]" journalOrPublisher="Contribuicoes Avulsas do Instituto Oceanografico, Universidade de Sao Paulo" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="1 - 146" part="20" refId="ref54902" refString="Tommasi, L. R. (1970) Os ofiuroides recentes do Brasil e de regioes vizinhas. Contribuicoes Avulsas do Instituto Oceanografico, Universidade de Sao Paulo, 20, 1 - 146." title="Os ofiuroides recentes do Brasil e de regioes vizinhas" type="journal article" year="1970">Tommasi 1970</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Thomas, L. P." box="[697,854,1614,1639]" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of Marine Science" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="232 - 247" part="25" refId="ref54734" refString="Thomas, L. P. (1975) The systematic relationships of Ophioplocus, Ophioceramis, and Ophioceres (Echinodermata, Ophiuroidea). Bulletin of Marine Science, 25, 232 - 247." title="The systematic relationships of Ophioplocus, Ophioceramis, and Ophioceres (Echinodermata, Ophiuroidea)" type="journal article" year="1975">Thomas 1975</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,1470,1963]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1650,1675]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Comments.</emphasis>
Young specimens (less than 
<quantity box="[669,756,1650,1675]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.6" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" unit="mm" value="7.6">7.6 mm</quantity>
of dd) have been considered difficult to identify due to the presence of fewer arm spines, fewer tentacle scales, and less fragmentation of dorsal arm plates (
<bibRefCitation author="Thomas, L. P." box="[1263,1424,1686,1711]" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of Marine Science" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="232 - 247" part="25" refId="ref54734" refString="Thomas, L. P. (1975) The systematic relationships of Ophioplocus, Ophioceramis, and Ophioceres (Echinodermata, Ophiuroidea). Bulletin of Marine Science, 25, 232 - 247." title="The systematic relationships of Ophioplocus, Ophioceramis, and Ophioceres (Echinodermata, Ophiuroidea)" type="journal article" year="1975">Thomas 1975</bibRefCitation>
). These characters have prompted many authors to describe new species and genera (
<bibRefCitation author="Lyman, T." bookContentInfo="203 pp." box="[1104,1252,1722,1747]" journalOrPublisher="University Press: Welch, Bigelow, &amp; Company, Cambridge" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" refId="ref50591" refString="Lyman, T. (1865) Ophiuridae and Astrophytidae. University Press: Welch, Bigelow, &amp; Company, Cambridge, 203 pp." title="Ophiuridae and Astrophytidae" type="book" year="1865">Lyman 1865</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Koehler, R." bookContentInfo="486 pp." box="[1265,1424,1722,1747]" journalOrPublisher="Government Printing Office, Washington" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" refId="ref49620" refString="Koehler, R. (1922) Ophiurans of the Philippine Seas and adjacent waters. Government Printing Office, Washington, 486 pp." title="Ophiurans of the Philippine Seas and adjacent waters" type="book" year="1922">Koehler 1922</bibRefCitation>
). During past decades, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lyman" authorityYear="1862" box="[402,545,1758,1782]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiuridae" genus="Ophioplocus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[402,545,1758,1782]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Ophioplocus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was alternately placed in two families, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Tommasi 1970)" authorityName="Tommasi" authorityYear="1970" baseAuthorityName="Tommasi" baseAuthorityYear="1970" box="[1014,1385,1758,1783]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiolepididae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="family">
Ophiolepididae (
<bibRefCitation author="Tommasi, L. R." box="[1204,1377,1758,1783]" journalOrPublisher="Contribuicoes Avulsas do Instituto Oceanografico, Universidade de Sao Paulo" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="1 - 146" part="20" refId="ref54902" refString="Tommasi, L. R. (1970) Os ofiuroides recentes do Brasil e de regioes vizinhas. Contribuicoes Avulsas do Instituto Oceanografico, Universidade de Sao Paulo, 20, 1 - 146." title="Os ofiuroides recentes do Brasil e de regioes vizinhas" type="journal article" year="1970">Tommasi 1970</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[151,277,1794,1819]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiuridae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="family">Ophiuridae</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Thomas, L. P." box="[296,459,1794,1819]" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of Marine Science" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="232 - 247" part="25" refId="ref54734" refString="Thomas, L. P. (1975) The systematic relationships of Ophioplocus, Ophioceramis, and Ophioceres (Echinodermata, Ophiuroidea). Bulletin of Marine Science, 25, 232 - 247." title="The systematic relationships of Ophioplocus, Ophioceramis, and Ophioceres (Echinodermata, Ophiuroidea)" type="journal article" year="1975">Thomas 1975</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Bernasconi, I. &amp; D'Agostino, M. M." box="[475,850,1794,1819]" journalOrPublisher="Revista del Museo Argentino de Ciencias Naturales &quot; Bernardino Rivadavia &quot;, Hidrobiologia" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="65 - 114" part="5" refId="ref44524" refString="Bernasconi, I. &amp; D'Agostino, M. M. (1977) Ofiuroideos del mar Epicontinental Argentino. Revista del Museo Argentino de Ciencias Naturales &quot; Bernardino Rivadavia &quot;, Hidrobiologia, 5, 65 - 114." title="Ofiuroideos del mar Epicontinental Argentino" type="journal article" year="1977">Bernasconi &amp; D’Agostino 1977</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Borges, M." bookContentInfo="143 pp." box="[866,1017,1794,1819]" journalOrPublisher="Universidade Estadual Paulista &quot; Julio de Mesquita Filho &quot;, Rio Claro" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" refId="ref44930" refString="Borges, M. (2006) Taxonomia, distribuicao e biologia reprodutiva de Ophiuroidea (Echinodermata) das Regioes Sudeste e Sul do Brasil. Phd thesis, Universidade Estadual Paulista &quot; Julio de Mesquita Filho &quot;, Rio Claro, 143 pp." title="Taxonomia, distribuicao e biologia reprodutiva de Ophiuroidea (Echinodermata) das Regioes Sudeste e Sul do Brasil" type="book" year="2006">Borges 2006</bibRefCitation>
). However, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lyman" authorityYear="1862" box="[1160,1303,1795,1819]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiuridae" genus="Ophioplocus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1160,1303,1795,1819]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Ophioplocus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Verrill" authorityYear="1899" box="[151,330,1830,1855]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Hemieuryalidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="family">Hemieuryalidae</taxonomicName>
due to its lateral arm plate morphology and molecular evidence (
<bibRefCitation author="O'Hara, T. D. &amp; Hugall, A. F. &amp; Thuy, B. &amp; Stohr, S. &amp; Martynov, A. V." box="[1059,1274,1830,1855]" journalOrPublisher="Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="415 - 430" part="107" refId="ref52377" refString="O'Hara, T. D., Hugall, A. F., Thuy, B., Stohr, S. &amp; Martynov, A. V. (2017) Restructuring higher taxonomy using broad-scale phylogenomics: The living Ophiuroidea. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution, 107, 415 - 430." title="Restructuring higher taxonomy using broad-scale phylogenomics: The living Ophiuroidea" type="journal article" year="2017">
O’Hara 
<emphasis box="[1151,1200,1830,1854]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">et al</emphasis>
. 2017
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lyman" authorityYear="1862" box="[1293,1436,1830,1854]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiuridae" genus="Ophioplocus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1293,1436,1830,1854]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Ophioplocus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs in colder and deeper waters at depths&gt; 
<quantity box="[680,738,1867,1891]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" unit="m" value="30.0">30 m</quantity>
and are often found with 
<taxonomicName authority="(Monteiro et al. 1992)" authorityName="Monteiro et al." authorityYear="1992" box="[1029,1432,1866,1891]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiodermatidae" genus="Ophioderma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1029,1171,1867,1891]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Ophioderma</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Monteiro, A. M. G. &amp; Reis, M. O. &amp; Pardo, E. V." box="[1186,1424,1866,1891]" journalOrPublisher="Boletim do Instituto Oceanografico, Universidade de Sao Paulo" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="39 - 53" part="40" refId="ref51816" refString="Monteiro, A. M. G., Reis, M. O. &amp; Pardo, E. V. (1992) Morfologia comparativa e distribuicao batimetrica de duas especies de Ophiuroidea, na regiao costeira de Ubatuba. Boletim do Instituto Oceanografico, Universidade de Sao Paulo, 40, 39 - 53. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / S 0373 - 55241992000100004" title="Morfologia comparativa e distribuicao batimetrica de duas especies de Ophiuroidea, na regiao costeira de Ubatuba" type="journal article" year="1992">
Monteiro 
<emphasis box="[1300,1349,1867,1891]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">et al</emphasis>
. 1992
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Currently, seven species are accepted in 
<taxonomicName authority="(Stohr et al. 2016)" authorityName="Stohr et al." authorityYear="2016" box="[609,970,1902,1927]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiuridae" genus="Ophioplocus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[609,752,1902,1926]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Ophioplocus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Stohr, S. &amp; Martynov, A." box="[768,962,1902,1927]" journalOrPublisher="PLoS ONE" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="0164562" part="11" refId="ref54292" refString="Stohr, S. &amp; Martynov, A. (2016) Paedomorphosis as an Evolutionary Driving Force: Insights from Deep-Sea Brittle Stars. PLoS ONE, 11, e 0164562. https: // doi. org / 10.1371 / journal. pone. 0164562" title="Paedomorphosis as an Evolutionary Driving Force: Insights from Deep-Sea Brittle Stars" type="journal article" year="2016">
Stöhr 
<emphasis box="[838,887,1902,1926]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">et al</emphasis>
. 2016
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, with one recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[1257,1325,1902,1927]" name="Brazil" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Barboza, C. A. M. &amp; Borges, M." journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="1 - 21" part="3447" refId="ref44247" refString="Barboza, C. A. M. &amp; Borges, M. (2012) A checklist of the extant species of ophiuroids (Echinodermata: Ophiuroidea) from Brazilian waters. Zootaxa, 3447, 1 - 21." title="A checklist of the extant species of ophiuroids (Echinodermata: Ophiuroidea) from Brazilian waters" type="journal article" year="2012">Barboza &amp; Borges 2012</bibRefCitation>
): 
<taxonomicName authority="(Lutken, 1856)" authorityName="Lutken" authorityYear="1856" baseAuthorityName="Lutken" baseAuthorityYear="1856" box="[345,648,1938,1963]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiodermatidae" genus="Ophioderma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="januarii">
<emphasis box="[345,470,1939,1962]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">O. januarii</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Lutken, C. F." box="[484,640,1938,1963]" journalOrPublisher="Vidensk Meddrfra dansk naturh, Foren" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="1 - 26" refId="ref50457" refString="Lutken, C. F. (1856) Bidrag til kundskab om Slangestjernerne. II. Oversigt over de vestindiske Ophiurer. Vidensk Meddrfra dansk naturh, Foren, 1 - 26." title="Bidrag til kundskab om Slangestjernerne. II. Oversigt over de vestindiske Ophiurer" type="book chapter" year="1856">Lütken, 1856</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
